                    <history>
                      <origin>
                        The <ref target="#coloph1">colophon</ref> states that the manuscript was completed in <origDate when="1912" evidence="internal-date"/>.
                        It was donated by <persName role="donor" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12978GabraSelassie">Gabra Śǝllāse</persName> 
                        to the church <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS1013FAG">Fārṭā ʾAdiko Gabrǝʾel</placeName>. The same person and church are also mentioned in 
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet120">Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth. 120</ref>.
                      </origin>
                      <provenance>According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
                        acquired by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4805Grebaut">Sylvain Grébaut</persName> in <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1216AddisA">ʾAddis ʾAbabā</placeName> 
                        in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                        <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                        The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhan),
                        Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot) and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                      </provenance>
                      <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date>18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
                    </history>
